Distribution. Unlike other species of the group, this taxon occurs in forest habitats of Brazil , in the Distrito Federal and the states of Minas Gerais, Rio de Janeiro, São Paulo, Paraná, Santa Catarina and Rio Grande do Sul, at elevations between 600–2000m (
Fig. 50
). Most specimens of this taxon ( circa 92 %) were registered between January and March (n= 90 ), similar to the temporal distribution of other species of the genus.
